@node "Usage" "Usage          "

 @{u}@{fg shine}USAGE@{uu}@{fg text}

    The commodity itself isn't all that hard to use, just run it. ;)
 The Prefs program is pretty straight forward as well. Double click
 to run it, use the defined hotkey, or the Show Interface button from
 a commodities exchange program.

 · FUNCTION - Select the function you would like to set the sample for.
   - keyboard 'F' will cycle through the functions.
 · VOLUME - Sets the volume for this event/sample.
   - keyboard 'v' will increase the volume, 'V' will decrease.
 · ENABLED/DISABLED - enables and disables this event.
   - keyboard 'd' will toggle. Checked is enabled, not checked is disabled.
 · L - this will provide file requester for you to select the sample to
       be played for this event.
   - keyboard 'l' will open the requester.
 · SAVE - Saves current settings and exits.
   - keyboard 's' will activate the changes and save.
 · CANCEL - Cancels all changes and exits.
   - keyboard 'c' will cancel all changed and exit.

   MENUITEMS
   SAVE - Saves all changes.
   ABOUT - shows you current version and author information.
   QUIT - exits the program w/o saving changes.

    WinSoundC itself can be enabled/disabled and removed via any
 commodities exchange compatable interface. Please see the history
 information for v1.1 for hints on when this commodity should be
 loaded and what can happen if it's not.
@endnode

@node "ToolTypes" "ToolTypes      "

 @{u}@{fg shine}TOOLTYPES@{uu}@{fg text}

 Supported ToolTypes:

 CX_PRIORITY - The priority of the commodity. Zero should
               be sufficient in almost all cases and you
               shouldn't need to change this, but it is
               supported nonetheless. :)

 HOTKEY - This is the hotkey that will activate the prefs
          program. The default value is "rawkey control lalt w"

 PREFS - This is the path to the prefs program. If not set, the
         default is Sys:Prefs/WinSoundPrefs.
@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation   "

 @{u}@{fg shine}INSTALLATION@{uu}@{fg text}


 Friendly Installation

    Run the Installer.

 Manual Installation

    This isn't really a hard thing to do. Just drag WinSoundPrefs
 program to sys:prefs and WinSound program to your WBStartup
 drawer and it will be ran upon every startup. Copy the WinSound.prefs
 to envarc:.
@endnode

@node "Features" "Features       "

 @{u}@{fg shine}WinSound features include@{uu}@{fg text}:

 · Makes use of datatypes for the loading of the
   audio files.

 · Settable hotkey for the prefs program.

 · Can be enabled/disabled/removed via any commodities
   exchange program. Can also be removed via CTRL-C.

 · Settable commodity priority

 · Easy to use prefs program which can be located
   anywhere using the PREFS @{"tooltype" link "ToolTypes" 0}.

 · Standard Installer® interface to ease @{"installation" link "Installation" 0}.

 NOTE:

 · Due to the way that workbench works some of the
   effects will NOT be played because workbench doesn't
   follow the standard vector calls like THEY wanted
   us to follow all the time. The effects that will not
   work (unless called via a program):
   
   · WindowToFront
   · WindowToBack
   · SizeWindow
   · ZoomWindow
   · OpenWindow() functions..most programs call OpenWindowTags()
     nowadays so I didn't bother to patch the OpenWindow() call.

 · These should work fine under other Workbench replacements
   if they ARE following the normal system calls like they
   should be per Commodores guidelines.
@endnode

